def: A native or natives of Ceylon descended from its primitiveinhabitants; also (sing.),
One of the movable, slender, spinelike organs or parts withwhich certain bryozoans are furnished. They are regarded as speciallymodified zooids, of nearly the same nature as Avicularia.
A youth; especially, a student in a german university.
The act or process of carding coarsely. Scribbing machine, themachine used for the first carding of wool or other fiber; -- calledalso scribbler.
The doctrine of nutrition; a treatise on nutrition.
In a stable manner; firmly; fixedly; steadily; as, a governmentstably settled.
The central chapel of the three forming the sanctuary of aCoptic church. It contains the high altar, and is usually closed byan embroidered curtain.
One who talks in the same strain or on the same subject untilweariness is produced. Richardson.
Any plant of a sweet taste.
A group of acalephs, including most of the larger jellyfishes;the Discophora.
